Certainly! Below is an example of a simple web app called "Handy's Mars Death Adventures" that is contained within a single HTML file. This app includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript to handle the functionality.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Handy's Mars Death Adventures</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #e63946;
        }

        .adventure {
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
        }

        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: none;
            background-color: #457b9d;
            color: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #1d3557;
        }

        .result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Handy's Mars Death Adventures</h1>
    <div class="adventure">
        <p>You are Handy, an astronaut on a perilous mission on Mars! What should you do?</p>
        <button id="explore">Explore the Martian Surface</button>
        <button id="stay">Stay in the Habitat</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result" id="result"></div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('explore').addEventListener('click', function() {
            let outcome = Math.random();
            if (outcome < 0.5) {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "You found some alien artifacts but got chased by rogue Martian creatures and narrowly escaped!";
            } else {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "Unfortunately, you encountered a sandstorm and got lost! You must return to the habitat.";
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('stay').addEventListener('click', function() {
            let outcome = Math.random();
            if (outcome < 0.5) {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "While staying safe in the habitat, you manage to gather enough data to save the mission!";
            } else {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "Sadly, a meteor shower hits your habitat and causes critical damage! You must make a quick escape.";
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions to Use

1. Copy the entire code above.
2. Paste it into a new file and save it with a `.html` extension, e.g., `handys_mars_adventures.html`.
3. Open the file using a web browser.

In this simple web app, you will find two options: "Explore the Martian Surface" and "Stay in the Habitat." Depending on your choice, you may encounter different outcomes, simulating Handy's adventures on Mars.
